<h1 class="text-2xl font-bold text-zinc-100 mb-6">Directory Structure</h1>

<p class="text-zinc-400 mb-6">
  The <code class="text-zinc-300 bg-zinc-800 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-sm">.botster/</code> directory
  holds all project and device configuration. It can exist at two levels.
</p>

<h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-zinc-200 mt-8 mb-3">Device level</h2>
<pre class="bg-zinc-900 border border-zinc-800 rounded-lg p-4 text-sm text-zinc-300 font-mono overflow-x-auto mb-6"><code>~/.botster/
  agents/
    claude/                          # Agent definition (AI-driven PTY)
      initialization                 # Startup script
  accessories/
    rails-server/                    # Accessory definition (plain PTY)
      initialization                 # Startup script
      port_forward                   # Enables port forwarding
  workspaces/
    dev.json                         # Workspace manifest (auto-spawn group)
  plugins/
    my-plugin/
      init.lua</code></pre>

<h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-zinc-200 mt-8 mb-3">Repo level</h2>
<pre class="bg-zinc-900 border border-zinc-800 rounded-lg p-4 text-sm text-zinc-300 font-mono overflow-x-auto mb-6"><code>your-repo/.botster/
  agents/
    claude/initialization            # Repo-specific agent config
  accessories/
    server/
      initialization
      port_forward
  workspaces/
    full-stack.json                  # Spawn agent + server together
  plugins/
    github/init.lua
    worktree-lifecycle/init.lua      # Worktree setup and cleanup (from template)</code></pre>

<p class="text-zinc-400">
  Repo-level config overrides device-level config for the same names. This lets you commit
  project-specific agent setup while keeping personal defaults at the device level.
</p>
